@{B}Escape Characters
=================@{UB}

Escape characters are supported as in the C++ language:

`\\\\n'
     newline character

`\\\\r'
     return character

`\\\\t'
     tab character

`\\\\h'
     horizontal tab character (V42.6)

`\\\\v'
     vertical tab character (V42.6)

`\\\\b'
     backspace character (V42.6)

`\\\\f'
     formfeed character (V42.6)

`\\\\"'
     double quote

`\\\\''
     single quote

`\\\\\\\\'
     backslash

`\\\\ooo'
     some octal number `ooo'. You can use `\\\\0' to get a NUL
     character. (V42.6)

`\\\\xXX'
     some hex number `XX'. (V42.6)

@{B}NOTE:@{UB} Depending on the AmigaGuide or MultiView version you are using,
you might see an additional backslash character where there should only
be one. This should show you one backslash: `\\\\'.  And this should
show two of them: `\\\\\\\\'.


@EndNode


